name: IllustratorSaveOptions

properties.description: What Illustrator file format version to create.
properties.name: compatibility

properties.description: Include a subset of fonts when less than this percentage of characters are used (version 9 or later)
properties.name: fontSubsetThreshold

properties.description: Embed the document's ICC profile in the saved file (version 9 or later)
properties.name: embedICCProfile

properties.description: Are linked image files to be included in the saved document (versions 7 or later)
properties.name: embedLinkedFiles

properties.description: How should transparency be flattened for older file format versions (pre-version 9)
properties.name: flattenOutput

properties.description: Save as a PDF compatible file (version 10 or later)
properties.name: pdfCompatible

properties.description: Should the saved file be compressed (version 10 or later)
properties.name: compressed

properties.description: All the artboards or range of the artboards will be saved.
properties.name: saveMultipleArtboards

properties.description: If SaveMultipleArtboards is true ,this will be considered for multi-asset extraction which specifies artboard range.Empty string will extracts all the artboards.Default is empty string.
properties.name: artboardRange

description: Options which may be supplied when saving a document as an Illustrator file.
